==========================================================
PURPOSE
==========================================================

This document defines the official Front-End standards for the NEXOTFE ERP.

Every page must follow these standards.

Consistency across the entire system is mandatory.

==========================================================
GENERAL PHILOSOPHY
==========================================================

NEXOTFE is a Premium Industrial ERP.

The interface must communicate:

Professionalism.

Engineering.

Organization.

Reliability.

Industrial identity.

The user must immediately recognize that every page belongs to the same system.

==========================================================
DESIGN PRINCIPLES
==========================================================

Every interface must prioritize:

Business productivity.

Visual consistency.

Easy navigation.

Fast data entry.

Low cognitive load.

Clear information hierarchy.

==========================================================
PAGE STRUCTURE
==========================================================

Every registration page follows the same structure.

Header

↓

Page actions

↓

Business cards

↓

Footer actions

Never create different layouts for similar pages.

==========================================================
HEADER STANDARD
==========================================================

Every page header must contain:

Page title.

Short description.

Current user.

Back button.

Home button.

Primary action button (Save, Create, Update, etc.).

The header must be identical throughout the system.

==========================================================
CARDS
==========================================================

Cards are the primary organizational element.

Rules:

Balanced proportions.

Compact height.

Consistent spacing.

Same border radius.

Same shadows.

Same internal padding.

Avoid oversized cards.

Avoid unnecessary empty space.

==========================================================
FORMS
==========================================================

Forms must follow a logical business sequence.

The most important information appears first.

Group related fields.

Avoid duplicated information.

Remove unnecessary fields.

Keep labels short and clear.

==========================================================
TABLES
==========================================================

Tables represent operational information.

Rules:

Occupy the available width.

No unnecessary horizontal scrolling.

Columns sized according to business importance.

Description fields receive more space.

Numeric fields remain compact.

Actions remain aligned.

Never distribute columns randomly.

==========================================================
BUTTONS
==========================================================

Buttons must have consistent behavior.

Primary action:

Blue.

Secondary action:

Neutral.

Danger actions:

Red.

Never use different colors for identical actions.

==========================================================
TYPOGRAPHY
==========================================================

Use clear hierarchy.

Page title:

Largest.

Card titles:

Medium.

Field labels:

Smaller.

Values:

Readable.

Avoid excessive bold text.

Bold is reserved only for information that truly requires emphasis.

==========================================================
SPACING
==========================================================

Spacing must be consistent.

Equal margins.

Equal paddings.

Balanced vertical rhythm.

Never leave unnecessary empty areas.

==========================================================
MODALS
==========================================================

Whenever possible,

related entity selection must occur inside a modal.

Examples:

Select Customer.

Select Supplier.

Select Product.

Select Resource.

Creating a new entity is always a secondary action.

==========================================================
LIST PAGES
==========================================================

List pages are operational screens.

They must prioritize:

Filtering.

Searching.

Quick actions.

Status visualization.

Fast navigation.

==========================================================
RESPONSIVENESS
==========================================================

The desktop experience is the primary target.

Responsive behavior must preserve usability without compromising productivity.

==========================================================
VISUAL CONSISTENCY
==========================================================

Never redesign a single page independently.

Every visual improvement must strengthen the overall identity of NEXOTFE.

The system must feel like one product.

Not multiple disconnected pages.

==========================================================
FINAL PRINCIPLE
==========================================================

Users should learn the interface only once.

After understanding one module,

they should immediately understand every other module.

Consistency is more valuable than visual novelty.